The Founder OF First City Monument Bank (FCMB) Group, Otunba Subomi Balogun, has said that having thoroughbred professionals around him as well as making God his priority made him to scale through the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) N25 billion recapitalisation policy. He added that the two factors have contributed immensely to his successes. He disclosed that during the recapitalisation, there were fears that his bank would not survive but providence had its way. Balogun, the President of Christian laities of ijebu land, while speaking at the yearly New Year prayer held at his residence in Ijebu-ode, attributed all his attainments in the banking sector to divine grace and reliance on professionals. 